# WordPress → Next migration (static phase)

## Goal

Replace the WordPress site with this Next.js project. In this phase, only **static pages and content** (HTML, SEO, layout)—no functional parity with the CMS or legacy business logic.

## Out of scope (do not implement unless explicitly requested)

- Database connectivity or data migration from WordPress
- Product catalog, pricing, inventory, or real e-commerce
- Cart, checkout, payments, or purchase sessions
- Sign-up/login, profiles, private areas, or user management
- Replicating WordPress plugins that depend on PHP, a database, or server-side logic

If the legacy site had those features, limit work to **static UI** (copy, public images, layout) or clear links/placeholders **without** persistence or APIs.

## Incremental strategy

- Migrate **one page at a time**: new routes under `app/…/page.tsx` (or whatever routing pattern this Next version uses).
- Extract repeated blocks into `components/` when it makes sense for the page being migrated.
- Do not carry over or re-enable the WordPress theme/global CSS; new styling uses Tailwind (see the `tailwind-migration` rule).

## Next.js in this repo

Before using Next/React APIs, follow `AGENTS.md` and the guide under `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` (conventions and deprecations for this version).
